t: A Song of degrees of David.
If*p it had not been the Lord*s who was on our side, now may Israel say;
If*p it had not been the Lord*s who was on our side, when men rose up against us:
Then*p they had swallowed us up quick, when their wrath was kindled against us:
Then*p the waters had overwhelmed us, the stream had gone over our soul:
Then*p the proud waters had gone over our soul.
Blessed*p be the Lord,*s who hath not given us as a prey to their teeth.
Our*p soul is escaped as a bird out of the snare of the fowlers: the snare is broken, and we are escaped.
Our*p help is in the name of the Lord,*s who made heaven and earth.
